(f)

We can reconstruct images by \(\tilde{x_i} = \bar{x} + \lambda_{i1}v_1+\lambda_{i2}v_2\).
By compare the original plot \(x_i\), average plot \(\bar{x}\), PC\(_1\), PC\(_2\), and the constructed plot \(\tilde{x_i}\), we can see that the first PC perfectly get the skew (rotation) and the width of the original character, but fail to capture the the size of the upper circle or lower circle.

# image reconstruction
x_tilde <- x_bar + y1[which.min(abs(y2))] * v1 +  y2[which.min(abs(y2))] * v2 

# plot comparison between original plot, average plot, PC1, PC2, reconstructed plot
mypar(mfrow = c(2, 3))
image(1:28, 1:28, z = matrix(data_sub[which.min(abs(y2)), ], nrow = 28, ncol = 28, byrow = F), col = gray((255:0) / 255), main = expression(x[i]))
image(1:28, 1:28, z = matrix(x_bar, nrow = 28, ncol = 28, byrow = F), col = gray((255:0) / 255), main = expression(bar(x)))
image(1:28, 1:28, z = matrix(v1, nrow = 28, ncol = 28, byrow = F), col = gray((255:0) / 255), main = expression(v[1]))
image(1:28, 1:28, z = matrix(v2, nrow = 28, ncol = 28, byrow = F), col = gray((255:0) / 255), main = expression(v[2]))
image(1:28, 1:28, z = matrix(x_tilde, nrow = 28, ncol = 28, byrow = F), col = gray((255:0) / 255), main = expression(tilde(x) ~ "by" ~ PC[1] ~ "&" ~ PC[2]))

(b)

  1. When \(q\) increase, the resolution of the image becomes higher and higher.
  2. The original image need \(200\times320 = 640,000\) pixels to store. When q = 50, we only need to store \(50\times 200 + 50\times320 + 50 = 26,050\) pixels.
# SVD on image
clown_svd <- svd(clown)

# reconstruct images using different q
q <- c(2, 5, 10, 20, 50, 100, 200)
mypar(mfrow = c(2, 4))
for (i in 1:8){
  if (i == 1){
    clown_hat_svd = clown
    plot.name <- "original"
  }
  else{
    clown_hat_svd <- (clown_svd$u)[, 1:q[i - 1]] %*% diag(clown_svd$d[1:q[i - 1]]) %*% t(clown_svd$v[, 1:q[i - 1]])
    plot.name <- paste0("rank = ", q[i - 1])
  }
  image(1:dim(clown)[2], 1:dim(clown)[1], z = t(clown_hat_svd), col = gray((255:0) / 255), main = plot.name)
}

(c)

# noncentered PCA
n <- dim(clown)[1]
clown_spectral_uncentered <- eigen(1 / (n-1) * t(clown) %*% clown)

# plot compressed images
nPC <- c(2, 5, 10, 20, 50, 100, 200)
mypar(mfrow = c(2, 4))
for (i in 1:8){
  if (i == 1){
    clown_hat_pca_uncentered = clown
    plot.name <- "original"
  }
  else{
    clown_hat_pca_uncentered <- t(clown_spectral_uncentered$vectors[, 1:nPC[i - 1]] %*% t(clown_spectral_uncentered$vectors[, 1:nPC[i - 1]]) %*% t(clown))
    plot.name <- paste0("# of PC = ", q[i - 1])
  }
  image(1:dim(clown)[2], 1:dim(clown)[1], z = t(clown_hat_pca_uncentered), col = gray((255:0) / 255), main = plot.name)
}

(d)

# centered PCA
clown_bar <- colMeans(clown)
clown_center <- t(t(clown) - clown_bar)
clown_spectral_centered <- eigen(1 / (n - 1) * t(clown_center) %*% clown_center)

# plot compressed imaged by centered pca
mypar(mfrow = c(2, 4))
for (i in 1:8){
  if (i == 1){
    clown_hat_pca_centered = clown
    plot.name <- "original"
  }
  else{
    clown_hat_pca_centered <- t(clown_spectral_centered$vectors[, 1:nPC[i - 1]] %*% t(clown_spectral_centered$vectors[, 1:nPC[i - 1]]) %*% t(clown_center) + clown_bar)
    plot.name <- paste0("# of PC = ", q[i - 1])
  }
  image(1:dim(clown)[2], 1:dim(clown)[1], z = t(clown_hat_pca_centered), col = gray((255:0) / 255), main = plot.name)
}

(e)

The larger the q, the smaller the SSE.
SVD SSE are almost the same with uncentered PCA SSE.
SVD SSE are larger than centered PCA SSE.

sse_results <- data.frame()
for (i in 1:7){
  clown_hat_svd <- clown_svd$u[, 1:q[i]] %*% diag(clown_svd$d[1:q[i]]) %*% t(clown_svd$v[, 1:q[i]])
  clown_hat_pca_uncentered <- t(clown_spectral_uncentered$vectors[, 1:q[i]] %*% t(clown_spectral_uncentered$vectors[, 1:q[i]]) %*% t(clown))
  clown_hat_pca_centered <- t(clown_spectral_centered$vectors[, 1:q[i]] %*% t(clown_spectral_centered$vectors[, 1:q[i]]) %*% t(clown_center) + clown_bar)
  sse_svd <- sum((clown - clown_hat_svd)^2)
  sse_pca_un <- sum((clown - clown_hat_pca_uncentered)^2)
  sse_pca <- sum((clown - clown_hat_pca_centered)^2)

  results <- data.frame(
  svd = sse_svd,
  pca_un = sse_pca_un,
  pca = sse_pca,
  row.names = q[i]
)

  sse_results <- rbind(sse_results, results)
}
sse_results
# Load the required package
library(tidyr)
## Warning: package 'tidyr' was built under R version 4.3.3
library(ggplot2)

# Convert the data frame from wide format to long format
sse_results$q <- row.names(sse_results)
long_sse_results <- tidyr::pivot_longer(sse_results, c("svd", "pca_un", "pca"), names_to = "method", values_to = "value")

# Define the order of the methods and q
method_order <- c("svd", "pca_un", "pca")
q_order <- q

# Convert method and q to ordered factors
long_sse_results$method <- factor(long_sse_results$method, levels = method_order)
long_sse_results$q <- factor(long_sse_results$q, levels = q_order)

# Create the scatter plot
ggplot(long_sse_results, aes(x = method, y = q, size = value)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.6) +
  scale_size(range = c(1, 10)) +
  labs(x = "Method", y = "q", size = "Value") +
  theme_minimal() + 
  guides(size = "none")
